DataElement.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the quantity in micrograms (ug) of the analyte.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Any material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes, including a sample obtained from a living organism or taken from the biological object after halting of all its life functions. Biospecimen can contain one or more components including but not limited to cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory products._The sample or material being subjected to analysis._A metric unit of mass equal to one millionth of a gram or one thousandth of a milligram._How much there is of something that you can measure; the total amount or number.
